I have the following parametrization of a curve (an ellipse): \begin{align}
x(t) &=\frac{-17(\cos(t)-\sqrt{2}\sin(t))+23}{6} \\
y(t) &=\frac{17(\cos{(t)}-\sqrt{2}\sin(t))+23}{6} \\ 
z(t) &=\frac{17\sqrt{2}\sin(t)+26}{6}
\end{align} for $0\leq t\leq2\pi$ . Now how can I calculate the distance from the point $(1,1,s)$ to this parametric curve in function only of $s$ ?

